'''Elfyn Lewis''' (born 1969)<ref name="BBCYP" /> is a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] painter who won the [[National Eisteddfod of Wales]] [[Gold Medal (National Eisteddfod of Wales)|Gold Medal for fine art]] in 2009 and the [[Welsh Artist of the Year]] prize in 2010.<ref name="BBC 2010">Laura Chamberlain (21 June 2010) [http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/wales/posts/elfyn_lewis_welsh_artist_of_the_year "Elfyn Lewis wins Welsh Artist of the Year prize"], [[BBC Wales]] blog. Retrieved 24 August 2013.</ref><ref name="Daily Post 2010">Kevin White (24 June 2010) [http://www.dailypost.co.uk/news/local-news/porthmadogs-elfyn-lewis-welsh-artist-2754200 "Porthmadog’s Elfyn Lewis is Welsh artist of the year"], [[Daily Post (North Wales)|''Daily Post'']] (North Wales). Retrieved 24 August 2013.</ref>

Lewis was born in [[Porthmadog]], [[Gwynedd]]<ref name="Daily Post 2010" /> and studied at the [[University of Central Lancashire]], [[Preston, Lancashire|Preston]], before gaining an MA in Fine Art from the [[University of Wales Institute, Cardiff]] in 1998.<ref name="WalesOnline Bylchau">Karen Price (19 February 2010) [http://www.walesonline.co.uk/lifestyle/showbiz/artist-preview-elfyn-lewis---1935991 "Artist Preview: Elfyn Lewis - Bylchau, St David’s Hall"], [[Wales Online]]. Retrieved 24 August 2013.</ref> He lives and works in [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]], [[Cardiff]].<ref>[http://www.elfynlewis.com/further-info.php Contact Info] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140112173432/http://www.elfynlewis.com/further-info.php |date=2014-01-12 }}, Elfynlewis.com. Retrieved 12 January 2014.</ref>

Lewis's paintings are held in the collections of the Cynon Valley Museum, [[MOMA, Wales|MOMA Wales]] and Gwynedd Museum and Art Gallery.<ref name="BBCYP">{{Art UK bio|retrieved=24 August 2013|ref=1}}</ref>

Elfyn Lewis was elected to the Royal Cambrian Academy, Conwy in 2017

