The '''Parents' Choice Award''' is an award presented by the [[non-profit]] Parents' Choice Foundation to recognize "the very best products for children of different ages and backgrounds, and of varied skill and interest levels."<ref name="pcf">{{cite web | url=http://www.parents-choice.org/aboutawards.cfm | title=Parents' Choice Awards | publisher=Parents' Choice Foundation | accessdate=2009-03-17}}</ref> It is considered a "prestigious" award among children's products,<ref>{{cite news | title=Books and Authors With Roots on the Island; Lending a Guiding Hand By Her Children's Books | url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E0DEFD81331F934A25752C0A96F958260 | first=Donna Kutt | last=Nahas | publisher=The New York Times | date=January 17, 1999 | accessdate=2009-03-17}}</ref> and has been described by the ''[[The Cincinnati Enquirer|Cincinnati Enquirer]]'' as the industry equivalent of an [[Academy Award]].<ref>{{cite news | title=Parents Can Consult Plenty Of `Top Toys' Lists | url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19951202&slug=2155479 | publisher=Cincinnati Enquirer (reprinted in Seattle Times) | first=Reon | last=Carter | date=December 2, 1995 | accessdate=2009-03-17}}</ref>{{not in citation|date=August 2017}}

The Parents' Choice Awards were established in 1978 by Diana Huss Green, who is currently the president of the Parents' Choice Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/cinar-receives-high-honors-from-the-parents-choice-foundation-in-the-us-77930382.html|title=CINAR receives high honors from the Parents' Choice Foundation|work=PR Newswire}}</ref> The award recipients are determined by a committee of educators, scientists, performing artists, librarians, parents and children. One of six award commendations are given to award winners: Classic, Gold, Silver, Recommended, Approved or "Fun Stuff."<ref name="pcf"/> The awards are held annually.

